  "title": "ISic003359. Ash chest for Gaius Matrinius Felicio",
  "body": "<div id=\"editions\"><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive\" lang=\"grc\">  <div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <a id=\"al1-interpretive\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">Γ(αι)</span> · <span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ματρίνι\"><span data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">Ματρίνι</span></span>  <br id=\"al2-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φηλικίων\"><span data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">Φηλικίων</span></span> · <br id=\"al3-interpretive\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρη(στὲ)</span> · <span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">καὶ</span> · <span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ἄμε(μπτε)</span> · <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-interpretive-simple-lemmatized\">  <div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-interpretive\">  <span data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">Γαι</span>  <span data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">Ματρίνι</span>  <span data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">Φηλικίων</span>  <span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">χρηστὲ</span>  <span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">καὶ</span>  <span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ἄμεμπτε</span>  <span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">χαῖρε</span>  </span></div>  <p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Jonathan Prag</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic\" lang=\"grc\"><div class=\"textpart\" lang=\"grc\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><a id=\"al1-diplomatic\"><!--0--></a><span class=\"linenumber\">1</span><span data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">Γ</span>·<span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Ματρίνι\"><span data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">ΜΑΤΡΙΝΙ</span></span><br id=\"al2-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">2</span><span data-type=\"name\" data-name-type=\"\" data-text=\"Φηλικίων\"><span data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">ΦΗΛΙΚΙΩΝ</span></span>·<br id=\"al3-diplomatic\"><span class=\"linenumber\">3</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗ</span>·<span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span>·<span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕ</span>·<span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div><div class=\"attribution\">Text encoding: Victoria Fendel, Robert Crellin</div><div id=\"edition-diplomatic-simple-lemmatized\"><div class=\"textpart\"><span class=\"ab\" id=\"div-diplomatic\"><span data-text=\"Γαι\" data-n=\"5\" data-lemma=\"Γαίους\">ΓΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"Ματρίνι\" data-n=\"15\" data-lemma=\"Ματρίνιος\">ΜΑΤΡΙΝΙ</span><span data-text=\"Φηλικίων\" data-n=\"20\" data-lemma=\"Φηλικίων\">ΦΗΛΙΚΙΩΝ</span><span data-text=\"χρηστὲ\" data-n=\"30\" data-lemma=\"χρηστός\">ΧΡΗΣΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"καὶ\" data-n=\"40\" data-lemma=\"καί\">ΚΑΙ</span><span data-text=\"ἄμεμπτε\" data-n=\"50\" data-lemma=\"ἄμεμπτος\">ΑΜΕΜΠΤΕ</span><span data-text=\"χαῖρε\" data-n=\"60\" data-lemma=\"χαίρω\">ΧΑΙΡΕ</span></span></div><p class=\"miniapp\"></p></div></div>  <div id=\"facsimile-images\"><h2>Facsimile Images</h2><a href=\"ISic003359_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003359.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359-thumb.jpg\"></a><a href=\"ISic003359_threequarter_tiled.tif\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_threequarter_tiled-thumb.tif\"></a><a href=\"ISic003359_threequarter.jpg\"><img title=\"Photo J. Prag, Aut. Assessorato Beni Culturali Regione Siciliana n.10681 del 06/05/2014\" src=\"ISic003359_threequarter-thumb.jpg\"></a></div>  <div id=\"apparatus\"><h4>Apparatus criticus</h4><ul><li><span>  <span>Text from autopsy</span>  </span></li></ul></div>  <div id=\"translation\"><h2>English translation</h2><p class=\"translation-author\"><a href=\"http://orcid.org/0000-0003-3819-8537\">Jonathan Prag</a></p>  <p>Gaius Matrinius Felicio, worthy and blameless, farewell!</p>  </div>  <div id=\"commentary\"><h2>commentary</h2>  <p>Φηλικίων presumably renders the Latin Felicio. Although the inscription is in Greek, it is noteworthy that it employs a Latin vocative form for Matrinius (implicit therefore also for Gaius), as well as abbreviating the formulaic words χρηστὲ and ἄμεμπτε, according to the more normal practices of Latin inscriptions; the use of interpuncts throughout is also distinctively Latin in practice. Ferrua suggests that the letters are of the end of the third century AD, but an earlier date also seems possible, and indeed likely.</p>  </div>  <div id=\"bibliography\"><h2>bibliography</h2>  <ul><li> Ferrua 1941 217 no.97 <a href=\"https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456\" target=\"_blank\">https://biblio.inscriptiones.org/epig10001456</a>  </li></ul>  <ul><li></li></ul>  </div>  <div id=\"handnote\"> <p>Somewhat irregular sized letters, not strictly following the horizontal. Pronounced but simple heavy serifs on deep v-cut letters. Alpha has extended top stroke, with cross-bar sloping down to the left; epsilon is lunate; kappa has short equal length arms; mu has four equal slopint strokes; rho has a large just closed eye; phi has ovoid body with standard height vertical; omega is cursive.</p> Lines 1-3  35-60  Interlineation line 1 to 2  not measured  </div><div id=\"license\"> Licensed under a Creative Commons-Attribution 4.0 licence. </div>",
  "divs": [
